{{Conservatism}}

'''美國保守主義'''（{{lang-en|American Conservatism}}）是[[美國|美國]]重要的[[政治哲学|政治哲学]]、[[社会哲学|社会哲学]]，其特徵包括尊重[[美国文化|美國傳統]]、支持{{tsl|en|Republicanism in the United States|美国共和主义|共和主义}}、[[古典自由主义|古典自由主义]]、限制联邦政府权力、提倡{{tsl|en|States' rights|州权}}、[[小政府|小政府]]。在美国，{{tsl|en|Media bias in the United States#Conservative|美国媒体偏见#保守主义|保守派媒体}}、{{tsl|en|Christian media|基督教媒体}}及{{tsl|en|List of American conservatives|美国保守主义者列表|保守主义者}}在政治中占有一席之地，[[兩黨制|两大党]]之一的[[共和黨_(美國)|共和党]]的主流意识形态亦为保守主义<ref name="Gramlich 2020">{{cite web | last=Gramlich | first=John | title=5 facts about Fox News |trans-title=关于福克斯新闻的5个事实| website=Pew Research Center | date=2020-08-18 | url=https://www.pewresearch.org/fact-tank/2020/04/08/five-facts-about-fox-news/ | access-date=2022-04-06}}</ref><ref name="The American Historian">{{cite web | title=Evangelicalism and Politics |trans-title=福音派与政治| website=The American Historian | url=https://www.oah.org/tah/issues/2018/november/evangelicalism-and-politics/ | access-date=2022-04-06}}</ref><ref name="Bivins 2018">{{cite web | last=Bivins | first=Jason C. | title=How Christian media is shaping American politics |trans-title=基督教媒体如何塑造了美国的政治 | website=The Conversation | date=2018-05-25 | url=http://theconversation.com/how-christian-media-is-shaping-american-politics-95910 | access-date=2022-04-06}}</ref>。

在社会议题上，美国保守派一般支持{{tsl|en|Christian ethics|基督教伦理|基督教价值观}}<ref name="Oxford UP"/>、[[道德绝对主义|道德绝对主义]]<ref>{{cite book|title= American Conservatism: History, Theory and Practice|trans-title=美国保守主义：历史、理论与实践|last= Farmer|first= Brian|publisher= Cambridge Scholars Publishing|year= 2005|isbn= 978-1904303541|location= United States|pages= 52|quote= To traditional conservatives, there most definitely are moral absolutes and they can most definitely and definitively identify those moral absolutes. [传统的保守派信仰道德绝对论，而且他们可以非常明确且肯定地确定存在绝对的道德。]}}</ref>、{{tsl|en|Family values|家庭价值|传统家庭观}}<ref name="wilcox">{{cite book|author=Clyde Wilcox|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GxdWDwAAQBAJ&pg=PT96|title=Onward Christian Soldiers?: The Religious Right in American Politics|trans-title=基督教士兵在前进？：美国政治中的宗教权利|publisher=Taylor & Francis|year=2018|isbn=9780429974533|page=96}}</ref>、[[美國例外論|美國例外論]]<ref>{{cite book|title= Superfluous Southerners: Cultural Conservatism and the South, 1920–1990|trans-title=多余的南方佬：文化保守主义与南方，1920–1990年|last= Langdale|first= John|publisher= University of Missouri Press|year= 2012|isbn= 9780826272850|location= United States|pages=4}}</ref>和[[个人主义|个人主义]]<ref name=":1">{{cite book|title= Liberal Hearts and Conservative Brains: The Correlation Between Age and Political Philosophy|trans-title=自由的心和保守的脑：年龄与政治哲学之间的相关性|last= Lipsman|first= Ron|publisher= United States|year= 2007|isbn= 9780595463206|location= United States|pages= 232|quote= The American conservative system of individualism, free markets, economic competition and deep respect for tradition... [美国的保守主义系统包含着个人主义、自由市场、市场竞争和尊重传统……]}}</ref>，反对{{tsl|en|United States anti-abortion movement|美国反堕胎运动|堕胎}}和[[同性婚姻|同性婚姻]]<ref name="jillson"/>。在经济议题上，美国保守派一般[[资本主义|亲资本]]<ref>Comparative Studies in Society and History. Vol. 29, No. 2 (Apr. 1987), p. 245. Cambridge University Press.</ref>、亲[[商业|商业]]、反[[工会|工会]]。在国家议题上，美国保守派一般支持强化[[國家安全|國家安全]]、支持{{tsl|en|Right to keep and bear arms in the United States|美国持有和携带武器的权利|持枪权}}和[[自由貿易|自由貿易]]<ref name=":0">{{cite book|title= Congressional Trade Votes: From NAFTA Approval to Fast-track Defeat|trans-title=国会贸易投票：从批准北美自由贸易区到快速通道的失败|last= Baldwin|first= Robert|publisher= [[彼得森国际经济研究所|Peterson Institute for International Economics]]|year= 2000|isbn= 9780881322675|location= [[美国|United States]]|pages= [https://archive.org/details/congres_bal_2000_00_4343/page/30 30]|quote= Conservatism generally is associated with pro-business, anti-labor, and strong-national-defense stances, all of which lead to support for free trade principles. [保守主义通常持亲商业、反工人及支持强化国家安全的立场，所有这些都导向支持自由贸易原则。]|url= https://archive.org/details/congres_bal_2000_00_4343/page/30}}</ref>，保護[[西方文化|西方文化]]免受[[共产主义|共产主义]]<ref>{{cite book|title= Debating the American Conservative Movement: 1945 to the Present |trans-title=辩论美国的保守主义运动：1945年至今|last= Critchlow|first= Donald|publisher= Rowman & Littlefield Publishers|year= 2009|isbn= 978-0742548244|location= United States|pages= 15|quote= Conservatives had a fear of Communism shared by most Americans. During this time a popular anti-Communist culture emerged in America, evident in movies, television programs, community activities, and grassroots organizations. This popular anti-Communist culture generated patriotic rallies, parades, city resolutions, and an array of anti—Communist groups concerned about Communist influence in the schools, textbooks, churches, labor unions, industry, and universities. [保守派对共产主义的恐惧是大多数美国人所共有的。这一时期的美国出现了一种流行的反共文化，在电影、电视节目、社区活动和基层组织中都有体现。这种流行的反共文化产生了爱国集会、游行、城市决议，以及一系列关注共产主义在学校、教科书、教堂、工会、工业和大学中产生的影响的反共团体。]}}</ref>和[[道德相对主义|道德相对主义]]<ref>{{cite book|title= Anglo-American Conservative Ideology After the Cold War |trans-title=冷战后的英美保守主义意识形态|last= Pilbeam|first= Bruce|publisher= Palgrave Macmillan|year= 2003|isbn= 978-0333997659|location= United States|pages= 100|quote= For most conservatives, if there is a common culprit in explaining society's descent into moral chaos, then it is relativism—the notion that there are no absolute values or standards, merely different interpretations and perspectives. [对大多数保守派来说，如果有什么能解释一切社会混乱的根源，那一定指的是相对主义——没有绝对价值或标准，只有不同解释和观点的思想。]}}</ref>的威胁。相较温和派和自由派而言，保守派不太相信[[科学|科学]]，尤其不相信[[医学|医学]]、[[气候学|气候学]]和[[演化|演化]]，而倾向于相信[[創造論|創造論]]<ref>"The Reason Why Some Republicans Mistrust Science: Their Leaders Tell Them To", Naomi Oreskes, Scientific American, 2021-06, https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/the-reason-some-republicans-mistrust-science-their-leaders-tell-them-to/</ref><ref>[https://oxford.universitypressscholarship.com/view/10.1093/oso/9780190944681.001.0001/oso-9780190944681 "Science Denial: Why It Happens and What to Do About It" <nowiki>[否认科学：为什么会发生这种情况以及该如何应对]</nowiki>], Gale Sinatra and Barbara Hofer, Oxford Scholarship Online, 2021-08, {{ISBN|978-0190944681}}, {{doi|10.1093/oso/9780190944681.001.0001}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Jones |first1=Jeffrey |title=Democratic, Republican Confidence in Science Diverges - Gallup |trans-title=民主党和共和党对科学的信心出现分歧 - 盖洛普 |url=https://news.umich.edu/study-evolution-now-accepted-by-majority-of-americans/ |access-date=2021-07-16}}</ref>。

歷史學家認為1790年代以來，保守主義傳統在美國政治和文化中扮演重要作用。然而有組織的[[保守主義|保守主義]]運動在政治中扮演關鍵作用則是1950年代之後的事情<ref name="Patrick Allitt 2009">Patrick Allitt, ''The Conservatives: Ideas and Personalities Throughout American History'', p. "before the 1950s there was no such thing as a conservative ''movement'' in the United States.", Yale University Press, 2009, ISBN 978-0-300-16418-3</ref><ref name="Kirk, Russell 1953">Kirk, Russell. ''The Conservative Mind: From Burke to Eliot'' (1953) traced a continuous tradition since the 1790s.</ref><ref name="Nicol C. Rae 1994 66">{{cite book|author=Nicol C. Rae|title=Southern Democrats|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8ZYgKHHpu9QC&pg=PA66|year=1994|publisher=Oxford U.P.|page=66|access-date=2016-11-14|archive-date=2020-06-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200626090436/https://books.google.com/books?id=8ZYgKHHpu9QC&pg=PA66|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 概述 ==
美国保守主义史中包含着许多冲突和彼此间竞争的意识形态。[[財政保守主義|財政保守主義者]]和[[自由意志保守主義|自由意志保守主義者]]拥护[[资本主义|资本主义]]、[[个人主义|个人主义]]、[[小政府|小政府]]和[[自由放任|自由放任]]，因此支持[[减税|减税]]、[[自由市場|自由市場]]、{{tsl|en|deregulation|去监管化}}、[[私有化|私有化]]、削减{{tsl|en|government spending|政府开支}}和[[公债|政府债务]]<ref name="google.com">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sq-1z8VMhDEC&dq=Modern+Political+Philosophy&pg=PA37|title=Modern Political Philosophy|trans-title=现代政治哲学|first=Richard|last=Hudelson|year= 1999|publisher=M.E. Sharpe|isbn=978-0765600219|via=Google Books}}</ref><ref name="dickerson">M. O. Dickerson et al., ''An Introduction to Government and Politics: A Conceptual Approach'' (2009) p. 129.</ref>。

{{tsl|en|Social conservatism in the United States|美国社会保守主义|社会保守主义者}}认为植根于宗教的传统社会价值观受到[[世俗主义|世俗主义]]和[[道德相对主义|道德相对主义]]威胁。他们倾向于支持{{tsl|en|School prayer in the United States|美国学校祷告|学校内的祷告活动}}和[[學券制|基督教学校内的學券制]]；{{tsl|en|United States anti-abortion movement|美国反堕胎运动|反对堕胎}}、[[社會對同性戀的態度|同性婚姻]]和{{tsl|en|Transgender rights in the United States|美国跨性别权利|跨性别者权利}}<ref>{{cite web|title=The Way We Live Now: On Language; Guns, God And Gays|trans-title=我们现在的生活方式：关于语言、枪支、上帝和同性恋者|author=Safire, William|date=2004-01-25|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2004/01/25/magazine/the-way-we-live-now-1-25-04-on-language-guns-god-and-gays.html|work=[[纽约时报|The New York Times]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://projects.essex.ac.uk/ehrr/V3N1/Afshar.pdf|title=Ahoura Afshar, "The Anti-gay Rights Movement in the United States: The Framing of Religion," ''Essex Human Rights Review'' (2006) 3#1 pp. 64–79}}</ref><ref>Glenn Utter and Robert J. Spitzer, ''Encyclopedia of Gun Control & Gun Rights'' (2nd ed. 2011)</ref><ref name="jillson">{{Cite book|author=Cal Jillson|title=Texas Politics: Governing the Lone Star State|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fQFZCrbc9mIC&pg=PA87|year=2011|publisher=Taylor & Francis|page=87|quote=Social conservatives focus on moral or values issues, such as abortion, marriage, school prayer, and judicial appointments. [社会保守派关注道德问题和价值观问题，如堕胎、婚姻、学校内的祷告活动和司法任命等。]|isbn=9780203829417}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|author1=John Anderson|author2=University of North Carolina John Anderson|title=Conservative Christian Politics in Russia and the United States: Dreaming of Christian Nations|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PISQBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA136|year=2014|publisher=Routledge|isbn=978-1-317-60663-5|page=136}}<br />{{cite book|author1=Amy Lind|author2=Stephanie Brzuzy|title=Battleground: M-Z|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=B-1icAV_xusC&pg=PA508|year=2008|publisher=Greenwood Publishing Group|isbn=978-0-313-34039-0|page=508}}<br />{{cite book|author=Kenneth M. Cosgrove|title=Branded Conservatives: How the Brand Brought the Right from the Fringes to the Center of American Politics|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ELgdJRIhX-cC&pg=PA27|year=2007|publisher=Peter Lang|isbn=978-0-8204-7465-6|page=27}}<br />{{cite book|author=Steven L. Danver|title=Encyclopedia of Politics of the American West|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UCRzAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA262|year= 2013|publisher=Sage Publications|isbn=978-1-4522-7606-9|page=262}}</ref>

[[新保守主義|新保守主義者]]想要将他们心目中的美国理念扩展到全世界<ref>Bruce Frohnen, ed. ''American Conservatism: An Encyclopedia'' (2006) pp. ix–xiv</ref>，[[旧保守主义|旧保守主义者]]则支持限制移民、[[不干預主義|不干预政策]]，{{tsl|en|opposition to multiculturalism|对多元文化的反对运动|反多元文化}}<ref name="Paleoconservative2">{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hqbHa_AJrtMC&q=paleoconservative%20immigration&pg=PA318 |title =American credo: the place of ideas in US politics|author=Michael Foley|publisher=[[牛津大學出版社|Oxford University Press]]|year= 2007 |quote=Against accusations of being pre-modern or even anti-modern in outlook, paleoconservatives press for restrictions on immigration, a rollback of [[多元文化主義|multicultural]] programmes, the decentralization of the federal polity, the restoration of controls upon free trade, a greater emphasis upon economic nationalism and [[孤立主义|isolationism]] in the conduct of American foreign policy, and a generally ''revanchist'' outlook upon a social order in need of recovering old lines of distinction and in particular the assignment of roles in accordance with traditional categories of gender, ethnicity, and race.|isbn =9780191528330}}</ref>。除一些自由意志保守主义者外，大多数保守主义者支持[[單邊主義|单边]]外交政策，以及维持一支强大的军队。包括自由意志保守主义者在内，大多数保守主义者支持持枪权，并援引[[美國憲法第二修正案|美國憲法第二修正案]]为论据。20世纪50年代以来的保守主义运动试图将这些不同的派别聚集在一起，强调保守主义者需要团结起来，阻止“无神共产主义”蔓延<ref>Paul Gottfried, ''Conservatism in America: Making Sense of the American Right'', p. 9, "Postwar conservatives set about creating their own synthesis of free-market capitalism, Christian morality, and the global struggle against Communism." (2009); Gottfried, ''Theologies and moral concern'' (1995) p. 12.</ref>。

